cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper deals with folding patterns and their geometric properties, such as flat-foldability and congruence of parallelograms. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper develops efficient algorithms for constructing minimum forcing sets and deciding whether a given set of creases is forcing or not. 
3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper studies the combinatorial properties of Miura-ori folding patterns, such as the size of forcing sets and the correspondence with $3$-colorings of grid graphs. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper may touch upon the computational complexity of the problems studied, such as the complexity of deciding whether a given set of creases is forcing or not. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper may have connections to game theory, as the folding of origami patterns can be seen as a game between the folder and the material.
